TITLE: Colorado businessman set for retrial over border wall fund
SUMMARY: Timothy Shea, a Colorado businessman, is back in New York to face a retrial on charges that he absconded with $25 million in an online crowdfunding campaign.

TITLE: NYC subway shove victim's mother says son ‘completely traumatized,’ ‘can’t move’
SUMMARY: The mother of the man seen on video being shoved onto the tracks at a subway station in Brooklyn last Friday is now speaking out in the wake of the brutal attack.

TITLE: Central US faces heavy rain, severe weather as storm system moves in
SUMMARY: Severe weather set to impact the central U.S. Monday will bring risks of heavy rain, strong winds and isolated tornadoes from the Southern Plains to the Tennessee Valley.

TITLE: Iran's assistance to Russia could make country an enemy combatant, missing family found and more top headlines
SUMMARY: ALLEGED WAR CRIMES - Iran's assistance to Russian war effort in Ukraine could make the country an enemy combatant, experts say

TITLE: The Army is scrapping Fort Hood. Here’s who it’ll be renamed after
SUMMARY: Fort Hood's new name commemorates the late war hero Richard Cavazos, a four-star Army general who served with honor, according to three retired Army generals.

TITLE: Michigan family of four that mysteriously disappeared one week ago is located in Wisconsin
SUMMARY: A Michigan family that disappeared on Oct. 16 after the father displayed "paranoia" during a 911 call was located in Wisconsin on Sunday, police announced.

TITLE: Michigan grandmother allegedly stabbed 2-year-old grandson in head, boy recovering in hospital
SUMMARY: A Michigan grandmother is accused of stabbing her 2-year-old grandson in the head multiple times. The boy is in stable condition in a local hospital.

TITLE: Virginia high school reports illness outbreak, 1,000 students call out sick
SUMMARY: Around 1,000 students and a few staff members at a Virginia high school called out sick last week after experiencing flu-like symptoms and stomach pains.

TITLE: Michigan woman arrested for failing to scan all items at Walmart self-checkout
SUMMARY: A Walmart in Michigan allegedly caught a woman stealing merchandise by not scanning every item, with the woman becoming agitated and leaving the store when confronted by employees.

TITLE: Buried car found in Silicon Valley mansion's front yard
SUMMARY: Police in Silicon Valley are investigating a situation where a car was discovered buried beneath the yard of a multi-million dollar home.
